def: A slip from a plant; a scion; a cutting. [R.] Holished.
One who lives at the same time with another; as, Petrarch andChaucer were contemporaries.
A double fluoride of zirconium and hydrogen, or some otherpositive element or radical; as, zircofluoride of sodium.
A marine bivalve shell belonging to the genus Arca and itsallies.
Pertaining to boxing, or to encounters with the fists;puglistic; as, fistic exploits; fistic heroes. [Colloq.]
Situated over, or on the dorsal side of, the sacrum.
